name: Sheri Ann Richerson
bio:
Sheri Ann Richerson is a leading pioneer in the self-sufficiency movement. For the past 19 years she has been living, teaching, and promoting organic gardening, natural health and self-sufficiency through all forms of media. Her career includes years as a nationally acclaimed best-selling author, radio host and guest on a variety of shows – showcasing her expertise on homesteading and gardening. Additionally, Ms. Richerson is a speaker, columnist and a blogger for hundreds of websites, magazines and newspapers. 

Ms. Richerson has been featured in The New York Times, Woman’s World Magazine and Ladies’ Home Journal. Her by-lined articles can be found at idiotsguides.com, Learn2Grow.com, Suite101.com, SFGate.com, eHow.com, GardenGuides.com and dozens of other sites.

name: || Elizabeth Rishel
bio:
Within the Grove was brought to life in May of 2015 to guide others on how they can turn a house into a home through DIY projects. By creating content for home decor, DIY, and lifestyle, WTG has become so much more the past 2 years! It’s a community where readers can feel at home and have a new sense of freedom when it comes to decorating and tackling home projects and life in general. Inspiration can be found several days a week on the blog through every part of life while turning your house into a home one project at a time. 

A little about me! I'm the creative director and writer behind the scenes of Within the Grove. I have a passion for living creatively and inspiring others to do the same. As a former teacher for nearly a decade, I can truly connect with my 
readers when showing budget friendly ways to decorate. I've been featured in Belong Magazine, OnlineLabels.com, Brit + Co., Craftgawker, and Homegawker. When not thrift shopping with a coffee in hand, you can find me enjoying everything Florida has to offer with my little family of three. Or to be honest, starting our next home project.

name: Jennifer Lind Schutsky
bio:
Jennifer is a Phoenix native, mother to two wild childs and married to her high school sweetheart. She graduated from The University of Arizona with a B.F.A. in Art education with an emphasis in painting in 2008. She is an Independent Artist + Photographer and Art Teacher. She loves to talk about all things natural, and is always planning her next family adventure. She started the blog hawks and honey to share about everyday life including her local food club project. H&H blossomed into not only a blog but added apparel line and wellness coaching. 

As an Art Educator she has always been creating, She started perusing photography more consistently in the past 2-3 years, second shooting weddings, lots of family and portrait sessions and mini sessions. She is also a Henna body artist, so her business is diverse. She manages a few projects turned businesses. 

Many Brands, One Mama. 

The unique thing about Jennifer is her business diversity, She loves photography and art so she's able to dabble in lots of aspects of those creative processes, which also allows for the times when photography is slow (hello Arizona summer) to focus on art and Henna. The variety of her businesses is key! 

She enjoys sharing her tips and tricks for managing income from multiple sources - especially important for those who are starting in photography but still working a day job. She wants to share about teamwork and how between her Husband and her they've found a a balance for managing childcare. She wants to help other mamas who feel like they have too much going on figure out where to focus, and she would like to inspire others to follow their creative interests and recognize how important it is to contribute to our communities.
